components.description:
Plays animation for a glTF asset. Also configures different settings for animation.
@param startTime World time at which animation started (ms since epoch)
@param pausedTime Paused location/time (sec) within animation track
@param playbackState Playback state of the animated entity
@param playbackType Playback type of the animated entity
@param track the animation track of the glTF to play

Audio component that can be attached to an entity. This component will play audio spatially from the entity.
@param file The Uri String of the audio file to be used
@param volume The volume of the audio to be played, default is 1.0f
@property audio The Uri String of the audio file to be used
@property volume The volume of the audio to be played, default is 1.0f

AvatarBody is a component that represents the body of an avatar. It contains references to the
head, left hand, right hand, and root of the avatar. It also contains a boolean flag to indicate
whether the avatar is player controlled.

@param head The head Entity of the avatar.
@param leftHand The left hand Entity of the avatar.
@param rightHand The right hand Entity of the avatar.
@param root The root Entity of the avatar.
@param isPlayerControlled A boolean flag to indicate whether the avatar is player controlled.

Defines the dimensions of a box shape by the relative offset of two opposite corners. A box of
max=Vector3(1,1,1) and min=Vector3(-1,-1,-1) will result in a 2x2x2 box. This is to be used with
the `mesh://box` `Mesh` URI.

@property min The relative offset of the bottom corner (furthest in the -x, -y, -z direction)
@property max The relative offset of the top corner (furthest in the +x, +y, +z direction)

Represents Controller Data and properties that can be used to facilitate input.

@param buttonState The current state of the buttons being pressed represented by integer bits
@param changedButtons Which buttons (represented by integer bits) have been changed (pressed or
unpressed)
@param isActive Whether the controller is active or not
@param type What type of controller it is: 0->controller 1->hand
@param directTouchEnabled Whether direct touch is enabled or not
@param directTouchButtonState The state of the direct touch buttons
@param laserEnabled Whether the laser is enabled or not

Defines the dimensions of a dome shape by a radius. This can be used for skyboxes.

@param radius The radius of the dome in meters
@property radius The radius of the dome in meters

Followable is a component that enables an entity to stay in front of another entity. Followable
will track the orientation of the parent and move itself to stay in front.

@param target Target Entity to follow
@param offset Pose offset to keep from target. Defining a quaternion will rotate the Entity
@param minAngle Minimum Y angle offset a followable will keep from target, 0 is straight ahead,
  positive values are up, negative values are down
@param maxAngle Maximum Y angle offset a followable will keep from target, 0 is straight ahead,
  positive values are up, negative values are down
@param type The behavior an object has when following (faces user, pivots on y axis, etc.)
@param tolerance This is the change in distance needed to start moving
@param speed How fast followable tracks to its desired location. Float value is a percent of
  default speed
@param active Whether entity is actively following or not

Grabbable is a component that allows an object to be grabbed by a controller. It requires the
Mesh Component to be present.

@param enabled Defines whether the object can be grabbed or not.
@param type The type of behavior an object has when grabbed (faces user, pivots on y axis, etc.)
@param isGrabbed Whether the object is currently grabbed or not
@param minHeight the minimum height an object can be held when grabbed
@param maxHeight the maximum height an object can be held when grabbed

Defines whether an object is hittable or not.

@param hittable The type of behavior the object can be hit using
@property hittable The type of behavior the object can be hit using

Panel is a component that can be attached to a scene object to indicate that it is a panel.

@param panelRegistrationId The id of the panel. This is used to identify the @PanelRegistration
  when creating the panel.
@param hittable hit test type for the panel, @see MeshCollision

PanelClickState is a component that is used to track the state of a panel click. It is used
in @see PanelClickSystem, and passes the state to the @see Panel component.

@param clickState The current state of the panel click.
@constructor Creates a new PanelClickState component with the specified click state.

PanelDimensions is a component that holds the dimensions of a panel. This is used to override the
height and width of a panel when creating the panel. Without it, the panel's height and width
will be the values from @see PanelRegistration.

@param dimensions The dimensions of the panel.
@property dimensions The dimensions of the panel.

Defines the dimensions of a horizontal plane.

@param width The width of the plane
@param depth The depth of the plane
@property width The width of the plane
@property depth The depth of the plane
@constructor Creates a plane with default width and depth of 1.0f

A Quad is a 2D shape that can be used to represent a 2D surface in 3D space. It is defined by its
minimum and maximum coordinates.

@param min The minimum coordinates of the Quad.
@param max The maximum coordinates of the Quad.
@property min The minimum coordinates of the Quad.
@property max The maximum coordinates of the Quad.
@constructor Creates a new Quad with the given minimum and maximum coordinates.

A ScenePlane is a 2D plane in the scene. It has a name, type, offset, and extents.

@param name The name of the plane.
@param type The type of the plane.
@param offset The offset of the plane.
@param extents The extents of the plane.

A SceneVolume is a 3D volume that can be used to represent a physical object in the scene.

@param name The name of the volume, identifier for the volume.
@param type The type of the volume, it will be used to determine a Anchor is belong to the volume
  or not.
@param offset The offset of the volume, all the Entity belongs to the volume will be offset by
  this value.
@param extents The extents of the volume

The component that defines the dimensions of a sphere by the radius. To be used with the
`mesh://sphere` `Mesh` URI.

@param radius The radius of the sphere in meters
@property radius The radius of the sphere in meters
@constructor Creates a sphere with the given radius
